== Dipping Sauce and Prep ==

Wash and dry produce.

Drain @Corn{1%unit}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve @Red Grapes{4.5%ounce} if desired. Thinly slice @Mini Cucumber{1%unit} into rounds.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Honey Dijon Dressing{1.5%ounce}, 1 TBSP BBQ sauce, and a pinch of @salt{}.

> For 6 servings: 4 TBSP dressing and 2 TBSP BBQ sauce instead.

== Fritter Batter ==

Roughly chop half the drained corn (all for 6 servings).

Add corn, @Riced Cauliflower{6%ounce}, @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded), and @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} to a #large bowl{}; stir to combine.

Stir in @Tempura Batter{82%g}, 1/3 cup cold water (2/3 cup for 6), 1/2 tsp salt (1 tsp for 6), and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Batter should be very thick but not dry; add a splash of water if necessary.

== Frying ==

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @Cooking Oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Once oil is shimmering and hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, carefully add heaping 1 1/2-TBSP scoops of batter to pan; press down lightly with a #spoon{}. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches, adding more oil in between each batch.

Transfer fritters to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Season with @salt{}.

> TIP: If fritters appear oily, pat dry with more paper towels.

== Serving ==

To serve: Divide fritters between plates. Serve with dipping sauce, grapes, cucumber, and @Sharp White Cheddar Snack Slices{3%unit} on the side.

To stash: Let fritters cool completely. Refrigerate fritters, dipping sauce, grapes, and cucumber in separate containers and pack with cheddar slices as desired!

== Chocolate Pudding ==

Combine @Semisweet Chocolate Chips{3%ounce} and @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon} in a second large #microwave-safe bowl{}; stir to coat. Add @Milk{2%unit} and 1/4 tsp salt; stir to combine.

Microwave, uncovered, until chocolate begins to melt, ~{1.5%minutes}. Gently whisk for ~{30%seconds}. Repeat microwaving and whisking 2-3 more times, until pudding begins to thicken and coats the back of a spoon.

> Keep a close eye on your bowl so it doesn't boil or overflow!

Carefully divide pudding between three small #serving bowls{} or #containers{}. Place a layer of #plastic wrap{} on top, directly touching the pudding (this helps prevent a solid layer from forming on top!), then cover bowls with another layer of plastic wrap.

Chill in the #refrigerator{} for at least ~{1%hour} or up to overnight. (Pudding will thicken as it cools.) Serve straight from the bowls!

> TIP: It's natural for the pudding to begin to separate as it sits. Simply re-whisk before serving!